Avail.name: Avail
Avail.description: An Avail describes the Availability Window of a specific Edit in a given country, which means the period Google is allowed to sell or rent the Edit. Avails are exposed in EMA format Version 1.6b (available at http://www.movielabs.com/md/avails/) Studios can see the Avails for the Titles they own. Post-production houses cannot see any Avails.

episodeTitleInternalAlias.name: episodeTitleInternalAlias
episodeTitleInternalAlias.description: OPTIONAL.TV Only. Title used by involved parties to refer to this episode. Only available on TV Avails. Example: "Coding at Google".

displayName.name: displayName
displayName.description: The name of the studio that owns the Edit referred in the Avail. This is the equivalent of `studio_name` in other resources, but it follows the EMA nomenclature. Example: "Google Films".

contentId.name: contentId
contentId.description: Title Identifier. This should be the Title Level EIDR. Example: "10.5240/1489-49A2-3956-4B2D-FE16-5".

seriesTitleInternalAlias.name: seriesTitleInternalAlias
seriesTitleInternalAlias.description: Title used by involved parties to refer to this series. Only available on TV Avails. Example: "Googlers, The".

seriesAltId.name: seriesAltId
seriesAltId.description: Other identifier referring to the series, as defined by partner. Only available on TV avails. Example: "rs_googlers".

availId.name: availId
availId.description: ID internally generated by Google to uniquely identify an Avail. Not part of EMA Specs.

videoId.name: videoId
videoId.description: Google-generated ID identifying the video linked to this Avail, once delivered. Not part of EMA Specs. Example: 'gtry456_xc'

seasonTitleInternalAlias.name: seasonTitleInternalAlias
seasonTitleInternalAlias.description: Title used by involved parties to refer to this season. Only available on TV Avails. Example: "Googlers, The".

episodeNumber.name: episodeNumber
episodeNumber.description: The number assigned to the episode within a season. Only available on TV Avails. Example: "3".

end.name: end
end.description: End of term in YYYY-MM-DD format in the timezone of the country of the Avail. "Open" if no end date is available. Example: "2019-02-17"

episodeAltId.name: episodeAltId
episodeAltId.description: Other identifier referring to the episode, as defined by partner. Only available on TV avails. Example: "rs_googlers_s1_3".

seasonAltId.name: seasonAltId
seasonAltId.description: Other identifier referring to the season, as defined by partner. Only available on TV avails. Example: "rs_googlers_s1".

titleInternalAlias.name: titleInternalAlias
titleInternalAlias.description: Title used by involved parties to refer to this content. Example: "Googlers, The". Only available on Movie Avails.

productId.name: productId
productId.description: Edit Identifier. This should be the Edit Level EIDR. Example: "10.2340/1489-49A2-3956-4B2D-FE16-6"

releaseDate.name: releaseDate
releaseDate.description: Release date of the Title in earliest released territory. Typically it is just the year, but it is free-form as per EMA spec. Examples: "1979", "Oct 2014"

formatProfile.name: formatProfile
formatProfile.description: Indicates the format profile covered by the transaction.

start.name: start
start.description: Start of term in YYYY-MM-DD format in the timezone of the country of the Avail. Example: "2013-05-14".

priceType.name: priceType
priceType.description: Type of pricing that should be applied to this Avail based on how the partner classify them. Example: "Tier", "WSP", "SRP", or "Category".

ratingReason.name: ratingReason
ratingReason.description: Value representing the rating reason. Rating reasons should be formatted as per [EMA ratings spec](http://www.movielabs.com/md/ratings/) and comma-separated for inclusion of multiple reasons. Example: "L, S, V"

priceValue.name: priceValue
priceValue.description: Value to be applied to the pricing type. Example: "4" or "2.99"

seasonNumber.name: seasonNumber
seasonNumber.description: The number assigned to the season within a series. Only available on TV Avails. Example: "1".

ratingSystem.name: ratingSystem
ratingSystem.description: Rating system applied to the version of title within territory of Avail. Rating systems should be formatted as per [EMA ratings spec](http://www.movielabs.com/md/ratings/) Example: "MPAA"

altId.name: altId
altId.description: Other identifier referring to the Edit, as defined by partner. Example: "GOOGLER_2006"

encodeId.name: encodeId
encodeId.description: Manifestation Identifier. This should be the Manifestation Level EIDR. Example: "10.2340/1489-49A2-3956-4B2D-FE16-7"

pphNames.name: pphNames
pphNames.description: Name of the post-production houses that manage the Avail. Not part of EMA Specs.

suppressionLiftDate.name: suppressionLiftDate
suppressionLiftDate.description: First date an Edit could be publically announced as becoming available at a specific future date in territory of Avail. *Not* the Avail start date or pre-order start date. Format is YYYY-MM-DD. Only available for pre-orders. Example: "2012-12-10"

ratingValue.name: ratingValue
ratingValue.description: Value representing the rating. Ratings should be formatted as per http://www.movielabs.com/md/ratings/ Example: "PG"

workType.name: workType
workType.description: Work type as enumerated in EMA.

storeLanguage.name: storeLanguage
storeLanguage.description: Spoken language of the intended audience. Language shall be encoded in accordance with RFC 5646. Example: "fr".

captionExemption.name: captionExemption
captionExemption.description: Communicating an exempt category as defined by FCC regulations. It is not required for non-US Avails. Example: "1"

territory.name: territory
territory.description: ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code for the country or territory of this Avail. For Avails, we use Territory in lieu of Country to comply with EMA specifications. But please note that Territory and Country identify the same thing. Example: "US".

captionIncluded.name: captionIncluded
captionIncluded.description: Communicating if caption file will be delivered.

Component.name: Component
Component.description: A Component is an element (audio, video, subtitle, artwork, trailer, etc...) that is used in a set of ExperienceLocales. A Component is owned by a Studio and managed either by the Studio itself or by one Post-Production House. Each Component is identified by a `component_id` and its `type`.

normalizedPriority.name: normalizedPriority
normalizedPriority.description: A simpler representation of the priority.

componentId.name: componentId
componentId.description: ID internally generated by Google to uniquely identify the Component. Example: 'wteyrc_647xc'

editLevelEidrs.name: editLevelEidrs
editLevelEidrs.description: List of Edit-level EIDR IDs. Example: "10.5240/1489-49A2-3956-4B2D-FE16-6".

altCutIds.name: altCutIds
altCutIds.description: List of Alternative Cut IDs, sometimes available in lieu of the main Edit-level EIDR IDs. This is not an EIDR ID, but a Partner-provided ID. Example: "206346_79838".

pphName.name: pphName
pphName.description: Name of the post-production house that manages the Component.

processingErrors.name: processingErrors
processingErrors.description: Processing errors during XML file parsing. Example: 'Invalid input file'

componentDetailType.name: componentDetailType
componentDetailType.description: Detail about the type of the Component.

studioName.name: studioName
studioName.description: Name of the studio that owns the Component.

customIds.name: customIds
customIds.description: List of custom IDs (defined by the partner) linked to the ExperienceLocale using this Component. Example: "R86241"

language.name: language
language.description: Language of the component, using the "BCP 47" format. Examples: "en", "en-US", "es", "es-419".

type.name: type
type.description: Type of the Component. Example: AUDIO_51

priority.name: priority
priority.description: Component priority, as defined by Google. The higher the value, the higher the priority.

elIds.name: elIds
elIds.description: IDs internally generated by Google to uniquely identify the ExperienceLocales for which the Component is used. Example: 'KRZiVjY9h7t'

titleLevelEidrs.name: titleLevelEidrs
titleLevelEidrs.description: List of Title-level EIDR IDs. Example: "10.5240/1489-49A2-3956-4B2D-FE16-5".

filename.name: filename
filename.description: File name of the Component when delivered.

playableUnitType.name: playableUnitType
playableUnitType.description: Type of the playable unit for which the Component is intended.

receivedTime.name: receivedTime
receivedTime.description: Timestamp when the Component was received.

approvedTime.name: approvedTime
approvedTime.description: Timestamp when the Component was approved.

name.name: name
name.description: Default Edit name, usually in the language of the country of origin. Example: "Googlers, The".

rejectionNote.name: rejectionNote
rejectionNote.description: Notes explaining why a Component has been rejected.

ExperienceLocale.name: ExperienceLocale
ExperienceLocale.description: An ExperienceLocale tracks the fulfillment of a Title in a country using a specific language, when delivered using component-based delivery. For example, a Title in Switzerland might have 3 ExperienceLocales: they both share the same country ("CH"), but each has different languages ("de", "fr", and "it"). Each ExperienceLocale is uniquely identified by an `el_id`, which is generated by Google. Externally, an ExperienceLocale can also be identified by partners using its EIDR IDs, AltCutID or `custom_id` (when provided).

country.name: country
country.description: Country where the ExperienceLocale is available, using the "ISO 3166-1 alpha-2" format. Example: "US".

normalizedPriority.name: normalizedPriority
normalizedPriority.description: A simpler representation of the priority.

studioName.name: studioName
studioName.description: Name of the studio that owns the ExperienceLocale.

customIds.name: customIds
customIds.description: List of custom IDs (defined by the partner) linked to this ExperienceLocale. Example: "R86241"

language.name: language
language.description: Language of the ExperienceLocale, using the "BCP 47" format. Examples: "en", "en-US", "es", "es-419".

videoId.name: videoId
videoId.description: Video ID, as defined by Google, linked to the feature video in the ExperienceLocale. Example: 'gtry456_xc'.

type.name: type
type.description: Type of the Edit linked to the ExperienceLocale.

priority.name: priority
priority.description: ExperienceLocale priority, as defined by Google. The higher the value, the higher the priority. Example: 90

elId.name: elId
elId.description: ID internally generated by Google to uniquely identify a ExperienceLocale. Example: 'KRZiVjY9h7t'

pphNames.name: pphNames
pphNames.description: Name of the post-production houses that manage the ExperienceLocale.

presentationId.name: presentationId
presentationId.description: PresentationID as defined in the EMA specs.

playableSequenceId.name: playableSequenceId
playableSequenceId.description: PlayableSequenceID as defined in the EMA specs.

altCutId.name: altCutId
altCutId.description: Alternative Cut ID, sometimes available in lieu of the main Edit-level EIDR ID. This is not an EIDR ID, but a Partner-provided ID. Example: "206346_79838".

inventoryId.name: inventoryId
inventoryId.description: InventoryID as defined in the EMA specs.

name.name: name
name.description: Default Edit name, usually in the language of the country of origin. Example: "Googlers, The".

approvedTime.name: approvedTime
approvedTime.description: Timestamp when the ExperienceLocale was approved.

createdTime.name: createdTime
createdTime.description: Timestamp when the ExperienceLocale was created.

trailerId.name: trailerId
trailerId.description: Trailer ID, as defined by Google, linked to the trailer video in the ExperienceLocale. Example: 'gtry457_tr'.

earliestAvailStartTime.name: earliestAvailStartTime
earliestAvailStartTime.description: Timestamp of the earliest start date of the Avails linked to this ExperienceLocale.

channelId.name: channelId
channelId.description: YouTube Channel ID linked to the ExperienceLocale. Example: "UCRG64darCZhb".

Order.name: Order
Order.description: An Order tracks the fulfillment of an Edit when delivered using the legacy, non-component-based delivery. Each Order is uniquely identified by an `order_id`, which is generated by Google. Externally, Orders can also be identified by partners using its `custom_id` (when provided).

orderedTime.name: orderedTime
orderedTime.description: Timestamp when the Order was created.

normalizedPriority.name: normalizedPriority
normalizedPriority.description: A simpler representation of the priority.

showName.name: showName
showName.description: Default Show name, usually in the language of the country of origin. Only available for TV Edits Example: "Googlers, The".

pphName.name: pphName
pphName.description: Name of the post-production house that manages the Edit ordered.

orderId.name: orderId
orderId.description: ID internally generated by Google to uniquely identify an Order. Example: 'abcde12_x'

episodeName.name: episodeName
episodeName.description: Default Episode name, usually in the language of the country of origin. Only available for TV Edits Example: "Googlers, The - Pilot".

studioName.name: studioName
studioName.description: Name of the studio that owns the Edit ordered.

legacyPriority.name: legacyPriority
legacyPriority.description: Legacy Order priority, as defined by Google. Example: 'P0'

videoId.name: videoId
videoId.description: Google-generated ID identifying the video linked to this Order, once delivered. Example: 'gtry456_xc'.

countries.name: countries
countries.description: Countries where the Order is available, using the "ISO 3166-1 alpha-2" format (example: "US").

type.name: type
type.description: Type of the Edit linked to the Order.

priority.name: priority
priority.description: Order priority, as defined by Google. The higher the value, the higher the priority. Example: 90

customId.name: customId
customId.description: ID that can be used to externally identify an Order. This ID is provided by partners when submitting the Avails. Example: 'GOOGLER_2006'

seasonName.name: seasonName
seasonName.description: Default Season name, usually in the language of the country of origin. Only available for TV Edits Example: "Googlers, The - A Brave New World".

receivedTime.name: receivedTime
receivedTime.description: Timestamp when the Order was fulfilled.

name.name: name
name.description: Default Edit name, usually in the language of the country of origin. Example: "Googlers, The".

approvedTime.name: approvedTime
approvedTime.description: Timestamp when the Order was approved.

channelName.name: channelName
channelName.description: YouTube Channel Name that should be used to fulfill the Order. Example: "Google_channel".

rejectionNote.name: rejectionNote
rejectionNote.description: Field explaining why an Order has been rejected. Example: "Trailer audio is 2ch mono, please re-deliver in stereo".

earliestAvailStartTime.name: earliestAvailStartTime
earliestAvailStartTime.description: Timestamp of the earliest start date of the Avails linked to this Order.

channelId.name: channelId
channelId.description: YouTube Channel ID that should be used to fulfill the Order. Example: "UCRG64darCZhb".

StoreInfo.name: StoreInfo
StoreInfo.description: Information about a playable sequence (video) associated with an Edit and available at the Google Play Store. Internally, each StoreInfo is uniquely identified by a `video_id` and `country`. Externally, Title-level EIDR or Edit-level EIDR, if provided, can also be used to identify a specific title or edit in a country.

country.name: country
country.description: Country where Edit is available in ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code. Example: "US".

hasAudio51.name: hasAudio51
hasAudio51.description: Whether the Edit has a 5.1 channel audio track.

hasInfoCards.name: hasInfoCards
hasInfoCards.description: Whether the Edit has info cards.

studioName.name: studioName
studioName.description: Name of the studio that owns the Edit ordered.

mid.name: mid
mid.description: Knowledge Graph ID associated to this Edit, if available. This ID links the Edit to its knowledge entity, externally accessible at http://freebase.com. In the absense of Title EIDR or Edit EIDR, this ID helps link together multiple Edits across countries. Example: '/m/0ffx29'

videoId.name: videoId
videoId.description: Google-generated ID identifying the video linked to the Edit. Example: 'gtry456_xc'

type.name: type
type.description: Edit type, like Movie, Episode or Season.

episodeNumber.name: episodeNumber
episodeNumber.description: The number assigned to the episode within a season. Only available on TV Edits. Example: "1".

audioTracks.name: audioTracks
audioTracks.description: Audio tracks available for this Edit.

showId.name: showId
showId.description: Google-generated ID identifying the show linked to the Edit. Only available for TV Edits. Example: 'et2hsue_x'

seasonId.name: seasonId
seasonId.description: Google-generated ID identifying the season linked to the Edit. Only available for TV Edits. Example: 'ster23ex'

seasonName.name: seasonName
seasonName.description: Default Season name, usually in the language of the country of origin. Only available for TV Edits Example: "Googlers, The - A Brave New World".

liveTime.name: liveTime
liveTime.description: Timestamp when the Edit went live on the Store.

hasHdOffer.name: hasHdOffer
hasHdOffer.description: Whether the Edit has a HD offer.

showName.name: showName
showName.description: Default Show name, usually in the language of the country of origin. Only available for TV Edits Example: "Googlers, The".

hasEstOffer.name: hasEstOffer
hasEstOffer.description: Whether the Edit has a EST offer.

seasonNumber.name: seasonNumber
seasonNumber.description: The number assigned to the season within a show. Only available on TV Edits. Example: "1".

hasVodOffer.name: hasVodOffer
hasVodOffer.description: Whether the Edit has a VOD offer.

pphNames.name: pphNames
pphNames.description: Name of the post-production houses that manage the Edit.

hasSdOffer.name: hasSdOffer
hasSdOffer.description: Whether the Edit has a SD offer.

name.name: name
name.description: Default Edit name, usually in the language of the country of origin. Example: "Googlers, The".

trailerId.name: trailerId
trailerId.description: Google-generated ID identifying the trailer linked to the Edit. Example: 'bhd_4e_cx'

quotaUser.description: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters.
